  "details": "<p class=\"mb-2\">WHAT IS VDM?</p><p class=\"mb-2\">SAP's Virtual Data Model standardizes CDS view development into</p><p class=\"mb-2\">layered view types. Following VDM ensures:</p><p class=\"mb-2\">✓ Consistent naming and structure across the organization</p><p class=\"mb-2\">✓ Clear separation of concerns between layers</p><p class=\"mb-2\">✓ Easier maintenance and onboarding of new developers</p><p class=\"mb-2\">✓ Reusable building blocks for Fiori, Analytics, and OData</p><p class=\"mb-2\">VDM VIEW TYPES:</p><p class=\"mb-2\">┌──────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────┐</p><p class=\"mb-2\">│ Type         │ Notation │ Purpose                        │</p><p class=\"mb-2\">├──────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────┤</p><p class=\"mb-2\">│ #BASIC       │ I_*      │ Interface - direct table access│</p><p class=\"mb-2\">│ #COMPOSITE   │ C_*      │ Business logic / calculations  │</p><p class=\"mb-2\">│ #CONSUMPTION │ C_*      │ Final layer for consumers      │</p><p class=\"mb-2\">│ #PRIVATE     │ P_*      │ Internal helpers (not consumed)│</p><p class=\"mb-2\">└──────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────┘</p><p class=\"mb-2\">BASIC VIEW CHARACTERISTICS:</p><p class=\"mb-2\">- Directly built on database tables or other #BASIC views</p><p class=\"mb-2\">- No/minimal business logic — pure data projection</p><p class=\"mb-2\">- Full field semantics (@Semantics.amount, @Semantics.date, etc.)</p><p class=\"mb-2\">- Named with I_ prefix in SAP standard: e.g. I_Travel_D</p><p class=\"mb-2\">- Foundation for all downstream composite/consumption views</p><p class=\"mb-2\">THIS EXAMPLE:</p><p class=\"mb-2\">@VDM.viewType: #BASIC  → Marks this as an Interface/Basic view</p><p class=\"mb-2\">@Analytics.dataCategory: #DIMENSION  → Used as a dimension in analytics</p><p class=\"mb-2\">@ObjectModel.dataType: #BASIC        → Core data type</p><p class=\"mb-2\">All fields have full @Semantics annotations (VDM requirement)</p><p class=\"mb-2\">DIAGRAM: assets/diagrams/vdm-layers.svg</p>",
